# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Logs
# Anything ending in .log is debug output from npm/yarn/pnpm
# or your own console.log dumps. Never useful in source control.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
lerna-debug.log*

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Dependencies & build output
# node_modules is huge and rebuilt by `npm install`.
# dist/ and build/ are produced by `npm run build` — every dev
# regenerates them locally.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
node_modules
dist
dist-ssr
build
*.local

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Environment variables (SECRETS — never commit)
# These hold your Supabase URL & anon key. Anyone with them can
# read/write your database. .env.example is the safe template
# (it has placeholder values only).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
.env.development
.env.production

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Build / dev-server caches
# Vite, TypeScript and ESLint all keep "I already did this"
# caches locally. They change every run and cause merge
# conflicts if committed.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.vite
.cache
.turbo
*.tsbuildinfo
.eslintcache

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Test coverage reports
# Vitest / Istanbul write HTML + JSON reports here. They are
# regenerated every test run.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
coverage
.nyc_output

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Editor / IDE files
# These are personal preferences — yours shouldn't be forced
# on the next developer. We keep .vscode/extensions.json so
# the team can share recommended extensions.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
.idea
*.suo
*.ntvs*
*.njsproj
*.sln
*.sw?

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OS-generated noise
# macOS, Windows and some Linux file browsers create these
# automatically when you preview folders. Pure clutter.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Editor / backup scratch files
# Vim, gedit, crash-recovery, ad-hoc backups, etc.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*~
*.bak
*.tmp
*.swp
*.swo

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Supabase CLI local state
# If you ever run `supabase start` locally, it drops state into
# these folders. We don't want per-machine state in git.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
supabase/.branches
supabase/.temp

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Accidental packaging artifacts
# `npm pack` produces .tgz files; sometimes folks zip the repo
# to email it. Don't commit those.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.tgz
*.tar.gz
*.zip

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Database seeds, dumps and backups
# We DO commit schema/migration SQL (spot-butchery-schema.sql,
# hardening.sql, inventory.sql, indexes/, policies/, etc.) so
# anyone can rebuild the database from scratch.
#
# But seed files and database dumps often contain real
# customer data (names, phone numbers, sales history). Those
# should NEVER hit a public git repo. They live on the laptop
# / Supabase project only.
#
# Naming convention:
#   *-seed.sql        → ignored  (starter rows you might tweak)
#   *_seed.sql        → ignored
#   *.seed.sql        → ignored
#   *-dump.sql        → ignored  (full DB exports)
#   *-backup.sql      → ignored
#   *.bak.sql         → ignored
#   supabase/seeds/   → ignored  (entire folder if it exists)
#   supabase/migrations-backup/ → ignored
#
# If you have a small set of default rows you DO want shared
# (e.g. default product categories), rename the file to
# something like `inventory-defaults.sql` and it stays tracked.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*-seed.sql
*_seed.sql
*.seed.sql
*-dump.sql
*_dump.sql
*-backup.sql
*.bak.sql
*.sql.gz
supabase/seeds/
supabase/migrations-backup/
